included.description:
Atlantic BT is a digital solutions provider that delivers enterprise-level critical web solutions to major companies across the world. As a UX Strategist at Atlantic BT, I worked collaboratively with our development and design teams to define and implement the processes that transform users' needs and clients' goals into exceptional user experiences. 

My specific duties included:
   
   â¢ Facilitating strategic user-centered design and decision making.
   â¢ Identifying UX requirements, setting goals, and researching users to help craft engaging experiences that balanced business objectives and users' needs.
   â¢ Maintaining and developing new UX capabilities by proposing and documenting relevant UX methodologies.
   â¢ Ad-hoc consultations on the appropriateness of specific UX research methodologies.
   â¢ Collaborating with development and design teams to create wireframes and functional prototypes.
   â¢ Developing information architectures, expert reviews, personas, scenarios and interaction models.

included.description:
Normal Modes is a user experience consultancy that offers a range of services including usability testing, user experience (UX) design, and user research training. During my time at Normal Modes I specialized in usability testing and user experience research for large, data-driven websites and applications that required users to complete complex processes like those found in oil trading applications, booking engines, eCommerce systems, and specialized portals. 

While at Normal Modes, I was the senior researcher responsible for managing our entire research contract life-cycle. My responsibilities included meeting with potential clients, generating requirements documents, designing research plans that met client objectives, writing contract proposals, and the implementation and oversight of said research plans. Post data collection I was responsible for the synthesis, preparation, and presentation of complex research results to clients and other stakeholders in which I provided actionable and prioritized design recommendations based on the user performance data we collected. 

I was also responsible for our community outreach and business development efforts for which I taught complex regulatory concepts (e.g., the Food and Drug Administrationâs [FDA] human validation testing guidelines) and research methodology courses via webinars and other e-media (e.g., blogs).
included.title: Senior User Experience Researcher

included.description:
During my time at the Houston VAâs Center for Innovations in Quality, Effectiveness and Safety, I was responsible for designing and delivering the patient-centered evaluations, via in-person and phone based patient interviews, of several health service interventions including a surgical oncology discharge intervention, a method of automating catheter-associated urinary tract infection reporting, and a hepatitis C shared decision making aid. 

As a member of these teams, I used my behavioral research expertise to help our investigators better understand the needs of patients and their medical providers. I also wrote and edited academic manuscripts, performed literature reviews using academic databases (e.g., PubMed, MEDLINE, EBSCOhost, and PsycInfo), and managed the activities of undergraduate medical students.

I also generally supported the research center by coordinating research activities, providing consultation on qualitative and quantitative research methodologies, and designing and structuring our data collection efforts including the data entry, maintenance, and query of large Microsoft Access databases.
included.title: Human Factors Psychologist

included.summary:
I have been a user experience researcher for over six years working with companies large and small including the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs, Hearst Corporation, Weatherford, Acuity Scheduling, and Fortinet. During that time I have had the privilege of working with and interviewing users from all across the country and in a variety of different contexts. Whether its surgical oncology patients, geologists on an oil rig out at sea, creative young professionals, older adults, small business executives, or industry leading CEOs, I have a passion for connecting organizations to the people who use their products and services. 

My specialties include research project management, cognitive interviewing, contextual inquiry, remote user testing, survey development, participatory design, competitive analysis, focus group moderation, card sorting, unmoderated testing, mobile device testing, heuristic evaluations, usability and A/B testing, persona development, task analysis, user research design, and working on a one-on-one basis with clients and other stakeholders to design qualitative and quantitative research designs that balance client objectives with scientifically rigorous research methodology.
